**JACoP Macro Question**

________________________________
From: Stefania Marcotti <stefania.marcotti@crick.ac.uk>
Sent: 09 April 2026 15:07
To: Freya Hoddle <freya.hoddle@crick.ac.uk>
Subject: Re: JACoP Macro Question

Hi Freya,

Please find attached a macro that should work. A few points to consider: 

  *
You might need to update the JaCOP plugin
  *
My test folder structure looks something like this. I'm saving the CSV (attached) in the folder called "output" [cid:bafef521-7e31-44eb-813c-d1780ee9d21e]
  *
JaCOP, out of the box, does not run on separate ROIs. I believe this is what was causing the issues. I'm now duplicating each ROI during the for loop (line 70) and creating a binary mask with Otsu thresholding then. Creating the binary mask allows me to set a consistent threshold in JaCOP when running the plugin, as all images at this stage will have values of either 0 or 255.   *
JaCOP output in the current version is in the Log, not as a results table (line 98). This means I need to clear the log after every run, which is not ideal. Please note that this is a bit of a quick and dirty solution, but considering the time constraints, it should do.   *
Should this go into a publication, please get in touch! We can help to make it publishable for better reproducibility. 

Please let me know if it works in your hands, and if you have any questions! Best wishes,
Stefania

________________________________
