From: Freya Hoddle <freya.hoddle@crick.ac.uk>
Sent: 09 April 2026 10:01
To: Stefania Marcotti <stefania.marcotti@crick.ac.uk>
Subject: JACoP Macro Question

Hello Stefania,

Thank you very much for offering your help. I am in a bit of a bind because this is they first time I have ever done something like this, and the revisions for the paper these results should feature in are due tomorrow - but obviously no worries if you don’t have time between now and tomorrow! 

Due to the time retraint I have mainly used AI to help me with this coding. For each image, I have a folder which includes a max projection .tif file with four channels, and a file with the manually-drawn ROIs saved. The macro is meant to open the max projection file, split the channels, close channels 2 and 4 (I only need to compare channels 1 and 3), and then run JACoP on each ROI to calculate the Pearson and Mander coefficients using Costes thresholding. It should then save these in a CSV file: 

// ----------------------
// Stage 3: Colocalization Analysis (Channels 1 & 3 Visible During Processing) // Uses saved max projection images and ROIs
// Calculates Pearson + Manders with Costes thresholding
// ----------------------

mainDir = getDirectory("Choose main folder containing subfolders"); subfolders = getFileList(mainDir);

// Choose folder to save CSV results
resultsDir = getDirectory("Choose folder to save results");

// Extract main folder name
splitDir = split(mainDir, "/");
mainFolderName = splitDir[splitDir.length-2];

// Automatically number results file
counter = 1;
resultsFile = resultsDir + mainFolderName + "_Coloc_C1_C3_results_" + counter + ".csv"; while (File.exists(resultsFile)) {
    counter++;
    resultsFile = resultsDir + mainFolderName + "_Coloc_C1_C3_results_" + counter + ".csv"; }

// Write CSV header
File.append("Folder,Image,Cell,PearsonR,M1,M2\n", resultsFile); 

// --- Disable batch mode so images are visible ---
setBatchMode(false);

for (s = 0; s < subfolders.length; s++) {

    subfolder = mainDir + subfolders[s];
    if (!File.isDirectory(subfolder)) continue;

    files = getFileList(subfolder);
    maxFile = "";
    roiFile = "";

    // Find max projection & ROI
    for (f = 0; f < files.length; f++) {
        if (endsWith(files[f], "_max.tif")) maxFile = subfolder + "/" + files[f];         if (files[f] == "ROIs.zip") roiFile = subfolder + "/ROIs.zip";     }

    if (maxFile == "" || !File.exists(roiFile)) {
        print("Skipping folder: " + subfolders[s] + " (missing max projection or ROIs)");         continue;
    }

    // --- Open max projection ---
    open(maxFile);
    imgTitle = getTitle();
    print("Processing: " + imgTitle);

    // --- Split channels ---
    run("Split Channels");

    // --- Close C2 and C4 if present ---
    if (isOpen("C2-" + imgTitle)) close("C2-" + imgTitle);
    if (isOpen("C4-" + imgTitle)) close("C4-" + imgTitle);

    // --- Rename C1 and C3 ---
    selectWindow("C1-" + imgTitle); rename("ch1");
    selectWindow("C3-" + imgTitle); rename("ch3");

    // --- Bring windows to front ---
    selectWindow("ch1");
    selectWindow("ch3");

    // --- Pause for verification ---
    waitForUser("Check that channels 1 and 3 are visible and named 'ch1' and 'ch3'. Click OK to continue."); 

    // --- Load ROIs ---
    roiManager("reset");
    roiManager("Open", roiFile);
    n = roiManager("count");

    // --- Apply 16-bit thresholding to ch1 & ch3 ---
    maxIntensity = 65535;
    selectWindow("ch1");
    setThreshold(0, maxIntensity-1);
    run("Convert to Mask");

    selectWindow("ch3");
    setThreshold(0, maxIntensity-1);
    run("Convert to Mask");

    // --- Run JACoP for each ROI ---
    for (r = 0; r < n; r++) {
        roiManager("select", r);

        // Trailing space required in plugin name
        run("JACoP ", "channel_1=ch1 channel_2=ch3 pearson manders costes"); 

        pearson = getResult("Pearson", nResults-1);
        m1 = getResult("M1", nResults-1);
        m2 = getResult("M2", nResults-1);

        line = subfolders[s] + "," + maxFile + "," + (r+1) + "," + pearson + "," + m1 + "," + m2 + "\n";         File.append(line, resultsFile);

        print("ROI " + (r+1) + " of " + n + " processed for " + imgTitle);     }

    // --- Close all images for this folder ---
    close("*");
}

// Channels 1 & 3 should already be closed by the above, but double-check if (isOpen("ch1")) close("ch1");
if (isOpen("ch3")) close("ch3");

print("Stage 3 complete. Results saved to: " + resultsFile);

Unfortunately, I always get an error:

Error: Image not found while running JACoP from a macro 1-Use "open(path)" in your macro to open images 2-Make sure you have called the right image ! in line 97: run ( "JACoP " , "channel_1=ch1 channel_2=ch3 pearson manders costes" <)> ; 

And unfortunately no matter what I do, I can’t seem to resolve this. I tried rooting directly the source files so JACoP can use those instead of finding the open channel windows, however this doesn’t work (according to the internet this is because I am running it on MacOS, although I have no idea if this is correct). 

Do you know how else I can bypass the JACoP plugin not recognising the open windows? 

Here is a Dropbox link which contains two of my test files, in two separate folders with their corresponding ROI file: 

<https://www.dropbox.com/scl/fo/yr3ogtayetur10y872uxm/AKyGBzGnCEw7FKo-ZjQ7_vU?rlkey=8b6767gzlftetrrmwyzy0xu34&dl=0> Dropbox<https://www.dropbox.com/scl/fo/yr3ogtayetur10y872uxm/AKyGBzGnCEw7FKo-ZjQ7_vU?rlkey=8b6767gzlftetrrmwyzy0xu34&dl=0> dropbox.com<https://www.dropbox.com/scl/fo/yr3ogtayetur10y872uxm/AKyGBzGnCEw7FKo-ZjQ7_vU?rlkey=8b6767gzlftetrrmwyzy0xu34&dl=0> [favicon.ico]<https://www.dropbox.com/scl/fo/yr3ogtayetur10y872uxm/AKyGBzGnCEw7FKo-ZjQ7_vU?rlkey=8b6767gzlftetrrmwyzy0xu34&dl=0> 

Thanks again!
Freya H

Freya Hoddle
PhD Student
Schumann Laboratory
The Francis Crick Institute
