From: Abena Amponsah <abena.amponsah@crick.ac.uk>
Date: Monday, 8 December 2025 at 14:39
To: Sara Salgueiro Torres <sara.salgueirotorres@crick.ac.uk>
Subject: It me again :)

Hi Sara,

Thank you for your help earlier.

I tried running the script on a larger data set and spotted some problems. I noticed the centroid (x,y coordinates) it provides for subsequent images are the same because it gets it from the same row. See below: 

    // Get the centroid coordinates
    x = getResult("X", 0);
    y = getResult("Y", 0);
    print("X is ", x);
    print("Y is ", y);

However, for image number 2, it won’t be row 1 as the result table would already have been populated from image one. I tried to overcome this by using the clear results & ROIR function after each image so that it can start afresh and always take it from the first row after each image but it doesn’t seem to be working properly. I think I’m missing something. 

Please see below the entire script. Any tips would be much appreciated. 

// Get input and output directories
inputDir = getDirectory("Choose Input Directory");
outputDir = getDirectory("Choose Output Directory");

// Get list of files in input directory
list = getFileList(inputDir);

// Process each file
for (i = 0; i < list.length; i++) {
  // Check if file is a TIFF image
  if (endsWith(list[i], ".tif")) {
    // Open image with Bio-Formats
    run("Bio-Formats", "open=[" + inputDir + list[i] + "] autoscale color_mode=Default open_all_series rois_import=[ROI manager] view=Hyperstack stack_order=XYCZT"); 

    // Apply Gaussian Blur
    run("Gaussian Blur...", "sigma=2");

    // Apply threshold
    setAutoThreshold("Li dark no-reset");
    setOption("BlackBackground", true);
    run("Convert to Mask");

    // Set measurements
    run("Set Measurements...", "area centroid center perimeter shape limit display add redirect=None decimal=3"); 

    // Measure the image to get the centroid
    run("Measure");

    // Get the centroid coordinates
    x = getResult("X", 0);
    y = getResult("Y", 0);
    print("X is ", x);
    print("Y is ", y);

//
getPixelSize(unit, pixelWidth, pixelHeight);
// replace with x & y pixelWidth & height
x_p =  x/pixelWidth;
y_p = y/pixelHeight;
   print("x_p is ", x_p);
  print("y_p is ", y_p);

    // Create point ROI at centroid
    makePoint(x_p, y_p, "small yellow hybrid");
    roiManager("Add");

    // Create bands around centroid
    for (j = 1; j <= 3; j++) {
      roiManager("Select", j-1);
      run("Enlarge...", "enlarge=100");
      roiManager("Add");
    }

    // Create XOR ROIs for each band
    roiManager("Select", newArray(0,1));
    roiManager("XOR");
    roiManager("Add");
    roiManager("Select", 4);
    roiManager("Rename", "100um");

    roiManager("Select", newArray(1,2));
    roiManager("XOR");
    roiManager("Add");
    roiManager("Select", 5);
    roiManager("Rename", "200um");

    roiManager("Select", newArray(2,3));
    roiManager("XOR");
    roiManager("Add");
    roiManager("Select", 6);
    roiManager("Rename", "300um");

    // Analyze particles in each band
    for (j = 4; j <= 6; j++) {
      roiManager("Select", j);
      run("Analyze Particles...", " show=[Overlay Masks] display summarize");     }

    // Save results to CSV file
    saveAs("Results", outputDir + list[i] + "_results.csv");

    // Save image with overlays
    run("Flatten");
    saveAs("Tiff", outputDir + list[i] + "_overlay.tif");

    // Close image
    run("Close");
  }
}

